<p>In honor of its past director, Dr. Larine Y. Cowan, the Office for Access and Equity (OAE) at the University of Illinois is proud to announce a call for nominations for the 2016 Larine Y. Cowan Make a Difference Awards. Consistent with its history in human rights advocacy, social justice, and diversity, OAE seeks to identify, recognize, and honor nominees who demonstrate exceptional dedication to and success in promoting diversity and inclusion through teaching, research, hiring practices, courses, programs, and events. </p>

<p>Nominations may be submitted by any member of the University community (co-worker, supervisor, adviser, dean or department head, student). Self-nominations are welcomed. </p>

